snippet.textDisplay:
I used to love a boy—and I still do. I had never listened to a Rajasthani song in my life, but I started listening because of him. We used to talk for a long time, and even before we got close, I already liked him. I never told him directly, but he knew. And I also felt that he liked me too—he did.

We used to talk every day. One day, we even went on a small trip together for three days. We weren’t officially in a relationship, but I was deeply in love. And somewhere deep down, I felt that he loved me too.

Those three days we spent together were beautiful—walking hand in hand in the mountains, holding each other gently, laughing together, looking into each other’s eyes... it was magical.

Now, there’s nothing left between us. Just memories.

When I hear this song, I imagine our wedding... but now, all that’s left are the memories.
